        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 3 at 3:38AM CDT until August 3 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 337 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Kingsmill, or 9
miles west of Pampa, moving southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pampa, Borger, Fritch, White Deer, Skellytown, and Kingsmill.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
